  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Pat your <strong>haddock bites </strong>dry with kitchen paper and season them with <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong> (unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite sized pieces!), then once the pan is hot, add the <strong>haddock bites </strong>and cook for 5 min, turning once halfway, until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>cooked haddock</strong> <strong>bites</strong> to a plate and reserve the pan</p><p>Add your <strong>linguine</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>linguine</strong> for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the<strong> linguine</strong> and set aside until later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the linguine is cooking, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your<strong> cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat (if it's looking a little dry, add a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong>)</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 1 min</p><p>Add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> with a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 2 min further</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your<strong> tomato paste</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> Chinese rice wine</strong> to the pan and cook for 30 secs, then pour in the <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Cook for 5-7 min or until reduced to a pasta sauce-like consistency</p><p>Remove from the heat and stir through a generous knob of <strong>butter </strong>with <strong>half</strong> of the<strong> chopped chives </strong>and a good grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained linguine</strong> and <strong>haddock bites</strong> to the sauce and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>haddock linguine with tomatoes & chilli</strong></p><p>Tip: If the sauce is too thin, return it to the heat and stir until the sauce sticks to the pasta</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/haddock-linguine-with-tomatoes-and-chilli/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> haddock linguine with tomatoes & chilli</strong> and sprinkle over the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped chives</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
